27/10/2005
WASHINGTON, United States -- President George W. 
Bush praised bilateral ties with Macedonia, telling Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski on Wednesday (26 October) that relations between their countries have "never been closer". 
The two leaders met under the framework of Buckovski's official weeklong visit to the US. 
According to Bush, Macedonia proved to be "a steadfast ally" through its commitment to international efforts against terrorists and on behalf of stabilising Afghanistan and Iraq. 
In turn, Buckovski thanked Bush for US support and reiterated Macedonia's desire to join NATO and the EU. 
(US Department of State, Makfax - 26/10/05)
